        "## 1. Data (→ thesis Ch. 3.1)\n",
        "\n",
        "**Primary measure — Garman–Klass realized-variance proxy** from daily Yahoo Finance OHLC, 2000 → present, for\n",
        "CAC 40 (`^FCHI`), DAX (`^GDAXI`), EURO STOXX 50 (`^STOXX50E`), FTSE 100 (`^FTSE`) and, as a control, the S&P 500 (`^GSPC`):\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\\widehat{GK}_t = \\tfrac{1}{2}\\big[\\ln(H_t/L_t)\\big]^2 - (2\\ln 2 - 1)\\big[\\ln(C_t/O_t)\\big]^2,\n",
        "\\qquad \\sigma_t = \\sqrt{\\widehat{GK}_t}, \\qquad x_t = \\log \\sigma_t .$$\n",
        "\n",
        "GK uses the full daily range and is ≈ 7–8× more efficient than squared close-to-close returns (Garman & Klass, 1980; Parkinson, 1980). We model **log realized volatility** $x_t$, following Andersen et al. (2003) and Gatheral et al. (2018).\n",
        "\n",
        "**Validation measure — true 5-minute realized variance** from a public GitHub mirror of the discontinued Oxford-Man Institute Realized Library (Heber et al., 2009): 8 indices, ≈ 2,615 trading days ending August 2022, no calendar dates (immaterial for scaling estimation, which only needs ordered trading days). Cite the mirror repository URL and your download date in Appendix E.\n",
        "\n",
        "Cleaning: drop rows with missing OHLC or non-positive $\\widehat{GK}_t$; indices with < 1,500 usable days are excluded with a warning."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Kv3IqiT53Qhh"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# --- 1. Load both data sources and build log-volatility series\n",
        "INDICES = {'.FCHI': 'CAC 40', '.GDAXI': 'DAX', '.STOXX50E': 'EURO STOXX 50',\n",
        "           '.FTSE': 'FTSE 100', '.SPX': 'S&P 500 (control)'}\n",
        "YF_TICKERS = {'.FCHI': '^FCHI', '.GDAXI': '^GDAXI', '.STOXX50E': '^STOXX50E',\n",
        "              '.FTSE': '^FTSE', '.SPX': '^GSPC'}\n",
        "MIRROR_URL = 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/bumhoson/SpilloverVolPrediction/main/rv_dataset.csv'\n",
        "\n",
        "def load_gk_logvol():\n",
        "    out = {}\n",
        "    for sym, tk in YF_TICKERS.items():\n",
        "        d = yf.download(tk, start='2000-01-01', auto_adjust=False, progress=False)\n",
        "        if isinstance(d.columns, pd.MultiIndex):\n",
        "            d.columns = d.columns.get_level_values(0)\n",
        "        d = d.dropna(subset=['Open', 'High', 'Low', 'Close'])\n",
        "        gk = 0.5 * np.log(d['High'] / d['Low'])**2 - (2*np.log(2) - 1) * np.log(d['Close'] / d['Open'])**2\n",
        "        gk = gk.replace([np.inf, -np.inf], np.nan).dropna()\n",
        "        gk = gk[gk > 0]\n",
        "        s = 0.5 * np.log(gk)          # log volatility = 0.5 * log variance\n",
        "        s.name = sym\n",
        "        if len(s) >= 1500:\n",
        "            out[sym] = s\n",
        "            print(f'  {sym:<10} {INDICES[sym]:<18} {len(s):>6} days   {s.index[0].date()} -> {s.index[-1].date()}')\n",
        "        else:\n",
        "            print(f'  WARNING: {sym} has only {len(s)} usable days -> excluded')\n",
        "    return out\n",
        "\n",
        "def load_mirror_logvol():\n",
        "    try:\n",
        "        m = pd.read_csv(MIRROR_URL, index_col=0)\n",
        "    except Exception as e:\n",
        "        print('  Mirror unavailable (roughness cross-check will be skipped):', e)\n",
        "        return {}\n",
        "    out = {}\n",
        "    for c in m.columns:\n",
        "        x = pd.to_numeric(m[c], errors='coerce').dropna()\n",
        "        x = x[x > 0]\n",
        "        if len(x) < 400:\n",
        "            continue\n",
        "        med = float(x.median())\n",
        "        vol = np.sqrt(x) if med < 1e-3 else x   # auto-detect variance vs volatility scale (H is invariant either way)\n",
        "        out[c] = pd.Series(np.log(vol.values), name=c)\n",
        "    print(f'  Mirror loaded: {len(out)} series, {len(next(iter(out.values()))) if out else 0} trading days each')\n",
        "    return out\n",
        "\n",
        "print('Primary (Garman-Klass proxy from Yahoo OHLC):')\n",
        "DATA = load_gk_logvol()\n",
        "print('Validation (5-min RV mirror, Oxford-Man lineage):')\n",
        "MIRROR = load_mirror_logvol()\n",
        "assert len(DATA) >= 3, 'Too few indices downloaded - check the internet connection and rerun this cell.'\n",
        "\n",
        "rows = []\n",
        "for sym, s in DATA.items():\n",
        "    ann_vol = float(np.exp(s).mean() * np.sqrt(252) * 100)\n",
        "    rows.append({'index': INDICES[sym], 'symbol': sym,\n",
        "                 'start': str(s.index[0].date()), 'end': str(s.index[-1].date()), 'N': len(s),\n",
        "                 'mean_logvol': round(float(s.mean()), 3), 'sd_logvol': round(float(s.std()), 3),\n",
        "                 'skewness': round(float(s.skew()), 3), 'excess_kurtosis': round(float(s.kurtosis()), 3),\n",
        "                 'annualized_mean_vol_pct': round(ann_vol, 1)})\n",
        "t31 = pd.DataFrame(rows)\n",
        "t31.to_csv(os.path.join(OUT, 'table_3_1_descriptives.csv'), index=False)\n",
        "t31"
      ],
