        "## 3. Is volatility rough? Moment-scaling estimation of H (→ thesis Ch. 3.3, RQ1)\n",
        "\n",
        "Following Gatheral, Jaisson & Rosenbaum (2018), for lags $\\Delta = 1,\\dots,50$ trading days and moments $q \\in \\{0.5, 1, 1.5, 2, 3\\}$ we compute\n",
        "\n",
        "$$m(q,\\Delta) = \\frac{1}{N_\\Delta}\\sum_t \\big|\\,x_{t+\\Delta} - x_t\\,\\big|^q,\n",
        "\\qquad \\log m(q,\\Delta) \\approx \\zeta_q \\,\\log \\Delta + c_q, \\qquad \\zeta_q \\approx qH .$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Linearity of $\\log m$ in $\\log\\Delta$ (Fig. 3.4) and of $\\zeta_q$ in $q$ (Fig. 3.5) supports fBm-like scaling; the common slope is the Hurst exponent $H$. We estimate $H$ by least squares of $\\zeta_q$ on $q$ through the origin, and report the dispersion of $\\zeta_q/q$ across $q$ as an internal-consistency band.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Sanity check** (do not skip): on the 5-min RV mirror, the S&P 500 should give $H \\approx 0.10\\!-\\!0.15$, in line with Gatheral et al. (2018). We run the estimator on **both** measures — the comparison speaks to the proxy-noise critique of roughness (\"fact or artefact\") discussed in the literature review. Note that $H$ is invariant to whether the mirror stores variance or volatility, since $\\log\\sqrt{v} = \\tfrac12\\log v$ shifts only the intercept $c_q$, never the slope $\\zeta_q$."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "6-tykh3x3uwK"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# --- 3. Roughness estimation (Figures 3.4 - 3.6, Table 3.2)\n",
        "QS = (0.5, 1.0, 1.5, 2.0, 3.0)\n",
        "DELTAS = np.arange(1, 51)\n",
        "\n",
        "def roughness(x, deltas=DELTAS, qs=QS):\n",
        "    x = np.asarray(x, dtype=float)\n",
        "    ld = np.log(deltas.astype(float))\n",
        "    zeta, fits = {}, {}\n",
        "    for q in qs:\n",
        "        m = np.array([np.mean(np.abs(x[d:] - x[:-d])**q) for d in deltas])\n",
        "        lm = np.log(m)\n",
        "        slope, intercept = np.polyfit(ld, lm, 1)\n",
        "        resid = lm - (slope*ld + intercept)\n",
        "        r2 = 1.0 - resid.var() / lm.var()\n",
        "        zeta[q] = slope\n",
        "        fits[q] = (ld, lm, slope, intercept, r2)\n",
        "    qa = np.array(qs); za = np.array([zeta[q] for q in qs])\n",
        "    H = float(np.sum(qa*za) / np.sum(qa*qa))     # LS slope through origin of zeta_q = q H\n",
        "    return {'H': H, 'H_sd': float((za/qa).std()), 'zeta': zeta, 'fits': fits,\n",
        "            'r2_mean': float(np.mean([fits[q][4] for q in qs]))}\n",
        "\n",
        "rough_rows, GK_FITS, GK_SUB = [], {}, {}\n",
        "for sym, s in DATA.items():\n",
        "    segments = [('full', s),\n",
        "                ('2000-2019', s[s.index < '2020-01-01']),\n",
        "                ('2020->',    s[s.index >= '2020-01-01'])]\n",
        "    for label, seg in segments:\n",
        "        if len(seg) < 400:\n",
        "            continue\n",
        "        r = roughness(seg.values)\n",
        "        rough_rows.append({'measure': 'Garman-Klass proxy', 'index': INDICES[sym], 'symbol': sym,\n",
        "                           'period': label, 'N': len(seg), 'H': round(r['H'], 4),\n",
        "                           'H_sd_across_q': round(r['H_sd'], 4), 'mean_R2': round(r['r2_mean'], 4)})\n",
        "        if label == 'full':\n",
        "            GK_FITS[sym] = r\n",
        "        GK_SUB[(sym, label)] = r['H']\n",
        "\n",
        "for sym, s in MIRROR.items():\n",
        "    r = roughness(s.values)\n",
        "    rough_rows.append({'measure': '5-min RV (mirror)', 'index': sym, 'symbol': sym,\n",
        "                       'period': 'full (~2012-2022)', 'N': len(s), 'H': round(r['H'], 4),\n",
        "                       'H_sd_across_q': round(r['H_sd'], 4), 'mean_R2': round(r['r2_mean'], 4)})\n",
