      "source": [
        "## 4. Forecasting design (→ thesis Ch. 4.1)\n",
        "\n",
        "Supervised windows per index: input = last $L = 63$ days of $x_t$; targets = $x_{t+1},\\dots,x_{t+5}$ (direct multi-horizon; we evaluate $h=1$ and $h=5$). Chronological **70 / 15 / 15** split into train / validation / test — no shuffling, standardization statistics fitted on the **training block only**, and the **same windows feed every model**, so forecast errors are exactly aligned observation-by-observation for the Diebold–Mariano tests.\n",
        "\n",
        "Benchmarks (→ Ch. 4.2), computed from the same 63-day context of each window:\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Naive / random walk:** $\\hat{x}_{t+h} = x_t$.\n",
        "- **HAR-RV** (Corsi, 2009), direct version per horizon $h$, by OLS:\n",
        "$$x_{t+h} = \\beta_0 + \\beta_d\\, x_t + \\beta_w\\, \\bar{x}^{(5)}_t + \\beta_m\\, \\bar{x}^{(22)}_t + \\varepsilon_{t+h},$$\n",
        "with $\\bar{x}^{(5)}_t$ and $\\bar{x}^{(22)}_t$ the 5- and 22-day context means."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "XjOVGt4w5HsE"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# --- 4. Windows and chronological splits (Table 4.2)\n",
        "def make_windows(values, L, Hh):\n",
        "    x = np.asarray(values, dtype=np.float32)\n",
        "    n = len(x) - L - Hh + 1\n",
        "    X = np.stack([x[i:i+L] for i in range(n)])\n",
        "    Y = np.stack([x[i+L:i+L+Hh] for i in range(n)])\n",
